267	  For a smooth morphism \(X \to \Spec(\bar k)\) and a point \(z \in X\), there is
268	  an affine open neighbourhood \(V \ni z\) and an \(\Gamma(\Spec \bar k, U)\)-algebra
269	  structure on \(\Gamma(X, V)\) making it a standard-smooth algebra, together with a
270	  witness that the stalk \(\mathcal O_{X, z}\) is the localisation of \(\Gamma(X, V)\)
271	  at the prime ideal corresponding to \(z\).
272	\end{lemma}
